name: (1,1'-biphenyl)-2,5-diol, diacetate
Reason: 1,1'-Biphenol has a melting point of around 50 degrees Celsius due to the presence of two phenyl groups, which increase the melting point due to their ability to enhance π-π interactions and overall molecular rigidity. Each phenyl group may contribute around +30 to +50°C. The diacetate group introduces two carbonyl groups, which can form strong hydrogen bonds and rigidify the structure, contributing around +20 to +40°C for each carbonyl.
